#: src/environment-variables.md:1
msgid "Environment variables"
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:3
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_LOG` (default: none). Enables Rustup's \"custom logging mode\". In "
"this mode, the verbosity of Rustup's log lines can be specified with "
"`tracing_subscriber`'s [directive syntax](https://docs.rs/tracing-subscriber/"
"latest/tracing_subscriber/filter/struct.EnvFilter.html#directives). For "
"example, set `RUSTUP_LOG=rustup=DEBUG` to receive log lines from `rustup` "
"itself with a maximal verbosity of `DEBUG`."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:8
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_HOME` (default: `~/.rustup` or `%USERPROFILE%/.rustup`). Sets the "
"root `rustup` folder, used for storing installed toolchains and "
"configuration options."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:12
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TOOLCHAIN` (default: none). If set, will [override](overrides.md) "
"the toolchain used for all rust tool invocations. A toolchain with this name "
"should be installed, or invocations will fail. This can specify custom "
"toolchains, installable toolchains, or the absolute path to a toolchain."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:17
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_DIST_SERVER` (default: `https://static.rust-lang.org`). Sets the "
"root URL for downloading static resources related to Rust. You can change "
"this to instead use a local mirror, or to test the binaries from the staging "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:22
msgid ""
"~~`RUSTUP_DIST_ROOT`~~ _deprecated_ (default: `https://static.rust-lang.org/"
"dist`). Use `RUSTUP_DIST_SERVER` instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:25
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_UPDATE_ROOT` (default `https://static.rust-lang.org/rustup`). Sets "
"the root URL for downloading self-update."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:28
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_VERSION` (default: none). Overrides the rustup version (e.g. "
"`1.27.1`) to be downloaded when executing `rustup-init.sh` or `rustup self "
"update`."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:31
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_IO_THREADS` _unstable_ (default: reported cpu count, max 8). Sets "
"the number of threads to perform close IO in. Set to `1` to force single-"
"threaded IO for troubleshooting, or an arbitrary number to override "
"automatic detection."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:36
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TRACE_DIR` _unstable_ (default: no tracing). Enables tracing and "
"determines the directory that traces will be written too. Traces are of the "
"form PID.trace. Traces can be read by the Catapult project [tracing viewer]"
"(https://github.com/catapult-project/catapult/blob/master/tracing/README.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:40
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TERM_COLOR` (default: `auto`). Controls whether colored output is "
"used in the terminal. Set to `auto` to use colors only in tty streams, to "
"`always` to always enable colors, or to `never` to disable colors."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:44
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_UNPACK_RAM` _unstable_ (default: free memory or 500MiB if unable to "
"tell, min 210MiB). Caps the amount of RAM (in bytes) `rustup` will use for "
"IO tasks while unpacking."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:47
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_NO_BACKTRACE`. Disables backtraces on non-panic errors even when "
"`RUST_BACKTRACE` is set."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:50
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_PERMIT_COPY_RENAME` _unstable_. When set, allows rustup to fall-back "
"to copying files if attempts to `rename` result in cross-device link errors. "
"These errors occur on OverlayFS, which is used by [Docker](https://docs."
"docker.com/storage/storagedriver/overlayfs-driver/#modifying-files-or-"
"directories). This feature sacrifices some transactions protections and may "
"be removed at any point. Linux only."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:56
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_AUTO_INSTALL` (default: 1) When set to `1`, installs the active "
"toolchain when it is absent. Set this value to `0` to disable automatic "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:60
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_HARDLINK_PROXIES` _unstable_. When set, rustup will not attempt to "
"symlink proxies and instead always use hardlinks. If you find this fixes a "
"problem, then please report the issue on the [rustup issue tracker](https://"
"github.com/rust-lang/rustup/issues)."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:64
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TERM_PROGRESS_WHEN` (default: `auto`). Controls whether progress "
"bars are shown or not. Set to `always` to always enable progress bars, and "
"to `never` to disable them."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:67
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TERM_WIDTH` (default: none). Allows to override the terminal width "
"for progress bars."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:69
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_DOWNLOAD_TIMEOUT` _unstable_ (default: 180). Allows to override the "
"default timeout (in seconds) for downloading components."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:72
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_CONCURRENT_DOWNLOADS` _unstable_ (default: 2). Controls the number "
"of downloads made concurrently."
msgstr ""

#: src/environment-variables.md:75
msgid ""
"`RUSTUP_TOOLCHAIN_SOURCE` _unstable_. Set by rustup to tell proxied tools "
"how `RUSTUP_TOOLCHAIN` was determined. Non-rustup tools should not set this "
"environment variable, except insofar as to mirror an earlier invocation from "
"rustup."
msgstr ""
